etymologies: early 19th century. From scientific Latin subiculum, probably from classical Latin subic-, stem of subicēs (plural) supports (from subicere to throw or place under) + -ulum

definitions: In certain fungi: a net-, felt-, or crust-like growth covering a substrate, consisting of a mat of hyphae from which fruiting bodies arise.
The parahippocampal gyrus of the cerebral cortex.
